"v.灌输；鼓励 【英】 v.灌输(instill; impart)；鼓励(inspire) 【考】 inspire : infuse / obliterate : remove(同义: 鼓舞=鼓舞/删除=去除 )反义词：drain away(排出); refuse(拒绝); extract(拔出) 【记】 in(进入)+fuse(流)→ 流进去→灌输 【例】 His speech infused the men with eagerness. v. (常与with连用)灌输 = instill = impart; 鼓舞(某人的勇气) 【记】in进入, fuse流－流进去－灌输 【类】inspire: infuse = obliterate: remove 鼓舞对鼓舞 = 删除对去除 【反】drain away(排出); refuse(vt 拒绝接受); extract(v 拔出) 【记】in 里 + fuse 流，向里流→灌输 【相关】confuse 都熔在一起了→使混淆，defuse 去掉雷管，diffuse 向外熔化流动→ 散开, 弥漫，effuse涌出流出，fuse 熔化成液体，熔合，雷管，引信，infuse 流入，interfuse 混合，perfuse 灌注，profuse充满，丰富，refuse 再熔化成没有的东西→废物，拒绝，suffuse 充满，transfuse 注入，灌输 infuse (v.)  early 15c., ""to pour in, introduce, soak,"" from Latin infusus, past participle of infundere ""to pour into,"" from in- ""in"" (see in- (2)) + fundere ""pour, spread"" (see found (v.2)). Figurative sense of ""instill, inspire"" first recorded 1520s (infusion in this sense dates from mid-15c.). Related: Infused; infusing."
